stream
BT /F1 12 Tf 44 720 Td (FeedOS Guide for Svivva + Pyracrypt) Tj
T*
T* (Purpose:) Tj
T* (Use deployed Svivva as the app shell, growth engine, marketing engine, and mini-app creation platform.) Tj
T* (Use Pyracrypt as the secure AI intelligence orchestration layer, model host, and data privacy service.) Tj
T*
T* (How to use Svivva now:) Tj
T* (1. Open your deployed Svivva front end on Vercel or your active domain.) Tj
T* (2. Treat Svivva as a single platform, not a separate app: it becomes the container for FeedOS intelligence.) Tj
T* (3. Use Svivva's existing page structure and content modules to add new feed, mood, analysis, and mini-app flows.) Tj
T*
T* (Svivva roles for FeedOS:) Tj
T* (- Growth engine: landing pages, referral gates, waitlists, onboarding funnels, share mechanics.) Tj
T* (- Marketing engine: auto-generated landing pages, social copy, email campaign drafts, SEO pages, campaign hooks.) Tj
T* (- Mini-app creation engine: build trend trackers, niche feeds, creator dashboards, research tools, mood feeds.) Tj
T* (- Automation layer: background queues, scheduled intelligence updates, prompt-driven content generation.) Tj
T* (- Experimentation platform: A/B page variants, feature tests, recommendation variants, campaign metrics.) Tj
T* (- AI workflow layer: connect model outputs, embeddings, feed scoring, and x-ray explanations into Svivva UI.) Tj
T*
T* (How to use Pyracrypt now:) Tj
T* (1. Use Pyracrypt as the backend service that manages secure AI model access and local model orchestration.) Tj
T* (2. Point Svivva AI-driven routes at Pyracrypt-hosted endpoints for transcription, embeddings, vision, and generation.) Tj
T* (3. Use Pyracrypt to keep your stack low-cost by running local open-source models instead of expensive cloud APIs.) Tj
T* (4. Use Pyracrypt for secure storage of API keys, prompt templates, and model metadata in a safe backend service.) Tj
T*
T* (Key FeedOS components to activate in Svivva:) Tj
T* (- Feed page: ingest content, show ranked discoveries, and surface recommendations.) Tj
T* (- Mood selector: let users pick modes like Deep Focus, Learning, Calm, Music, Fashion, Creative.) Tj
T* (- X-ray panel: display intent, emotion, credibility, repost risk, and recommendation reason.) Tj
T* (- Taste graph: show evolving personalization signals across colors, style, pace, humor, music energy.) Tj
T* (- Mini-app builder: generate specialized feeds and research tools from templates.) Tj
T* (- Analytics dashboard: track retention, engagement, saves, shares, conversion, and mini-app usage.) Tj
T* (- Daily brief: surface trends, top ideas, emerging creators, and niche opportunities.) Tj
T*
T* (Feeds, ingestion, and data sources:) Tj
T* (Start by wiring Svivva to the sources you can already support: YouTube, Reddit, RSS, podcasts, and user uploads.) Tj
T* (For MVP, prioritize sources with available RSS or public APIs, then add TikTok / Instagram / X later.) Tj
T* (Extract the content fields Svivva needs: titles, captions, descriptions, comments, transcripts, frames, image features.) Tj
T*
T* (AI stack strategy \(free / local first\):) Tj
T* (- Transcription: whisper.cpp locally or Faster-Whisper for audio/video transcript extraction.) Tj
T* (- Embeddings: sentence-transformers / all-MiniLM-L6-v2 for semantic search and taste matching.) Tj
T* (- Vision: CLIP, SigLIP, or Florence-2 for image and frame understanding.) Tj
T* (- Generation: Ollama local models using Llama 3 3B for fast responses, Qwen 8B for reasoning, Mistral Small for better text.) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
