4 0 obj
<< /Length 3453 >>
stream
BT /F1 12 Tf 44 720 Td (- Vector store: pgvector in Postgres for embeddings and similarity search.) Tj
T* (- Queue: BullMQ for background tasks and batch scoring.) Tj
T* (- Cache: Redis for session state, feed caches, and fast query results.) Tj
T* (- Database: PostgreSQL for user data, feeds, experiments, and analytics.) Tj
T* (- Auth: Clerk free tier for user sign-in and access control.) Tj
T*
T* (How to use Svivva to build FeedOS without coding the whole product from scratch:) Tj
T* (1. Identify the existing Svivva pages you can reuse and extend for the FeedOS experience.) Tj
T* (2. Add a dedicated integration module inside Svivva for FeedOS intelligence and Pyracrypt model orchestration.) Tj
T* (3. Build incrementally: first launch a feed page, mood selector, and X-ray panel; then add taste graphs and mini-app builder.) Tj
T* (4. Use Svivva's growth and marketing automation to launch each mini-app as a product experiment, not just a feature.) Tj
T*
T* (Mini-app ideas to deploy from Svivva:) Tj
T* (- Trend tracker: daily viral topic heatmap and content surge alerts.) Tj
T* (- Niche feed: curated recommendations for specific interests like fashion, streetwear, or micro-learning.) Tj
T* (- Creator dashboard: discovery score, audience fit, and creator growth signals.) Tj
T* (- Mood feed: personalized playlists for Creative Inspiration, Deep Focus, Calm, or Music Discovery.) Tj
T* (- Audience analyzer: sentiment, engagement style, and attention signals for a target segment.) Tj
T* (- Research lab: generate niche topic briefs, competitor summaries, and micro-trend insights.) Tj
T*
T* (Marketing and launch playbook:) Tj
T* (- Use Svivva to generate landing pages for each mini-app, then A/B test headlines and CTAs.) Tj
T* (- Create social content, email sequences, and TikTok scripts from the same AI engine that fuels FeedOS insights.) Tj
T* (- Build waitlists and referral incentives inside Svivva so each new mini-app can be promoted as a launch feature.) Tj
T* (- Track conversion events in the analytics dashboard and iterate on the highest-performing growth loop.) Tj
T*
T* (Practical MVP rollout in under 2 weeks:) Tj
T* (Week 1: wire data ingestion, launch one feed page, connect Pyracrypt AI generation, and set up user auth.) Tj
T* (Week 2: add mood selector, X-ray explanation layer, mini-app template, and marketing page with growth triggers.) Tj
T* (Keep scope narrow: one source, one mood feed, one marketing funnel, one analytics dashboard.) Tj
T*
T* (What to do immediately in the deployed app:) Tj
T* (- Use Svivva's existing deployment to host the front end and management UI.) Tj
T* (- Connect an active PostgreSQL + Redis environment via Vercel or Railway/Supabase to support FeedOS data and queues.) Tj
T* (- Use Pyracrypt for secure local model endpoints and prompt orchestration rather than expensive cloud AI services.) Tj
T*
T* (How to market this using Svivva and Pyracrypt together:) Tj
T* (- Sell FeedOS as an AI attention OS powered by Svivva's growth and mini-app engine.) Tj
T* (- Position Svivva as the platform and Pyracrypt as the intelligence / privacy layer.) Tj
T* (- Publish campaign pages, viral scripts, SEO tools, and creator showcases from Svivva's marketing engine.) Tj
T* (- Use mini-app releases to generate new launch moments and audience experiments.) Tj
T*
T* (Scale plan:) Tj
T* (- Keep the first launch cheap with local open-source models and Vercel free tier front end.) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
